The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) says it has granted the immediate former governor of Anambra State, Willie Obiano, bail. Chairman of the EFCC, Abdulrasheed Bawa, disclosed this to journalists in Abuja on Monday. Governor Willie Obiano He said this on the sideline of 5th Annual General Assembly (AGA) of the Network of Anti-Corruption Institutions in West Africa (NACIMA). Bawa said the former governor had been granted bail but added that he was still in custody because he had yet to perfect his bail conditions. He also dismissed claims that Obiano’s arrest was political, saying, “Nothing political about the arrest of the former Anambra State Governor, Wille Obiano. He has been granted bail. But we await (when) he fulfils his bail conditions.” Obiano was arrested last Thursday at about 8:30 pm by the anti-graft agency at Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos on his way out of the country. He was later moved to Abuja where he is being quizzed over alleged mismanagement of N42 billion and contract inflation.